          <note>A note about notes
----------------

 This is a note outlining good practice in note writing for SCUBA-2 MSBs. 
 PLEASE replace this note with your own note or delete altogether
 BEFORE submitting the MSB.


Things to include in your notes
-------------------------------

* Calibration details

1) Overall observing strategy for your science program. A paragraph
   conveying the general ideas behind your science program is useful
   for the observer (who may not be an expert in your field) and the
   TSS. (Check "show to the Observer").

2) Details of calibration observations.
   It is recommended that you always include a calibration observation in your
   MSB and mark it as such. The TSS will know whether a suitable calibration
   has been done and can defer it to later in the night if no calibration source
   is available.

   If you have a very exact calibration requirement make sure this note
   tells the TSS that you really want to calibrate a lot. You may even want
   to add a calibration observation after your science observation in that case.

   The TSS will take care of skydips and focussing. If you absolutely must
   focus or skydip before your observation include that in the MSB with a note.
   You will be charged for this additional overhead.

   If there is a specific source to be used for calibration make sure your
   calibration MSB includes that source.

   In short, you'll at least want something to check SCUBA-2's FCF, the
   conversion of instrument units to mJy/beam. Planets are our primary 
   calibrators and a library of secondary calibrators will become available over 
   time. Second you may want to monitor the sky using skydips: while water 
   vapor measurements and CSO tipper opacity measurements can be used to
   monitor trends, less frequent, but regular skydips can provide the absolute
   level as seen by the instrument. Note that the effective bandwidth of 
   SCUBA-2s filters will be opacity dependend, especially at 450um.
   
3) If you want a specific calibration measurement but only want it a few times for your run include it as a separate calibration MSB noting how often you want it to be done and that it should only be done when a science observation for your project has been observed. Calibration observations should be flagged as 'calibration' on their title page to prevent unnecessary repeats.</note>
          <title>Please read</title>
        </SpNote>
